  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 21 airports right now. Engine anti-ice operations are flagged at Göteborg Landvetter (GOT/ESGG). Across base airports: 6 critical, 12 high, 5 medium, 16 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Tirana International Airport Mother Teresa (TIA/LATI); plus 15 other bases. 5 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is thunderstorm / convective risk, low cloud base and snow / blowing snow  — most notably around Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD), Modlin (WMI/EPMO) and Budapest Liszt Ferenc (BUD/LHBP). Network hotspots: Göteborg Landvetter (GOT/ESGG), Bordeaux–Mérignac (BOD/LFBD), Cologne Bonn (CGN/EDDK), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Memmingen Allgau (FMM/EDJA) and 16 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and cold‑temperature performance penalties. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Göteborg Landvetter (GOT/ESGG), Bordeaux–Mérignac (BOD/LFBD), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH) and 9 others.",
